description.plain:
McBriare Samuel Lanyon (born Vernor Winfield McBriare Smith IV on April 30, 1990), better known by his stage name Mac DeMarco, is a Canadian singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and record producer.

Before branching out as Mac DeMarco, he first emerged under the moniker Makeout Videotape.

McBriare Samuel Lanyon (born Vernor Winfield McBriare Smith IV on April 30, 1990), better known by his stage name Mac DeMarco, is a Canadian singer-songwriter, multi-instrumentalist, and record producer.

Before branching out as Mac DeMarco, he first emerged under the moniker Makeout Videotape.

songs.full_title: Chamber of Reflection by Mac DeMarco
songs.title: Chamber of Reflection

description.plain:
Musically heavier than most of the songs on Salad Days, DeMarco mixes several things on this song. Starting from the topic about the Chamber of Reflection in the Mason Culture and his weird relationship with the fame portrayed in his “Macumentary”, Pepperoni Playboy.

The synth-part is borrowed from Japanese artist Shigeo Sekito’s song “The World II (ザ・ワードⅡ / セキトウ・シゲオ)”, which was released in 1975. Mac’s version was then sampled by Wiz Khalifa in “Smoke Chambers” and Mr. Waves in “Smooth Departure”.



The music video for the song contains the masonic compass and square with a G (stands for God or geometry). Which fits the imagery used in this song.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=kz9jhG963no

This is not the first time Mac has used masonic symbols, his first band Makeout Videotape’s album Ying Yang had many of those on its cover (the Eye of Providence, the square and the 33).

songs.full_title: My Kind of Woman by Mac DeMarco
songs.title: My Kind of Woman

description.plain:
Mac writes about a relationship between a boy who loves a girl, sees her as a reflection of him and loves her with with everything he has. With a semi-poignant ballad, Mac pleads with the girl to “show [him her] world, declaring that she is his "kind of woman”.

Mac has stated this song is about his girlfriend Kiera McNally, or Kiki.

https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wIuBcb2T55Q
